From 8cd8c97d519ae774448a265a675454cdaae11d20 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tam Nguyen <tam.nguyen.xa@renesas.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Aug 2022 05:30:42 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 10/15] uio: uio_pdrv_genirq: Add parameter to check device no
 clock

Some device has been not defined clock in DT but still execute test
so the patch to avoid that.

Signed-off-by: Tam Nguyen <tam.nguyen.xa@renesas.com>
---
 drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c b/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c
index 7ab557d338ac..bc3cede82d96 100644
--- a/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c
+++ b/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c
@@ -247,6 +247,12 @@ static int priv_clk_set_div(struct uio_info *info, int div)
 		return -EINVAL;
 
 	hw = __clk_get_hw(priv->clk);
+
+	if (!hw) {
+		dev_err(&priv->pdev->dev, "No define clock for device\n");
+		return -EINVAL;
+	}
+
 	value = clk_hw_get_flags(hw);
 	if (value & CLK_SET_RATE_PARENT)
 		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
-- 
